# The PrimeVue PT Law

## Integration Architecture

Our PrimeVue integration uses **Styled Mode** with a custom preset (`createCustomPreset`) defined in `src/utils/theme/primevuePreset`. This preset maps our CSS variable design tokens directly onto PrimeVue's internal theme contract. All PrimeVue components inherit brand colors, spacing, border radius, and dark mode variants automatically through this system.

Global pass-through presets live in `src/utils/theme/ptPresets/` (e.g., `formControlsPt.ts`). These are registered at the app level and apply to every instance of a given component type. **Always check if a global PT already covers your use case before writing a local one.**

## Ownership Boundary

- PrimeVue preset tokens own density and sizing: height, width, padding, gap, radius, action/dropdown button sizes, and size-mode variables.
- Global PT owns visual state and motion: semantic background/border/text classes, focus ring, disabled/invalid affordance, overlay material, and transition properties.
- Local `:pt` may only add non-conflicting visual/motion extensions. Do not use local PT to fight global token sizing.

---

## Step 0: Check Global PTs Before Writing Local Ones

Global pass-through presets are registered at app startup and cover the most common components:

```text
src/utils/theme/ptPresets/
  formControlsPt.ts     ← InputText, Textarea, Select, MultiSelect, DatePicker, etc.
  buttonPt.ts           ← Button variants
  dataTablePt.ts        ← DataTable rows, headers, pagination
```

Open the relevant preset before writing a local `:pt`. If global PT already styles the slot you need, do not duplicate locally.

---

## REQUIRED: Use `:pt` for All Component Customization

To customize any PrimeVue component beyond what the preset provides, you **MUST** use `pt` (Pass-Through). Combine with semantic UnoCSS tokens for dark-mode safety.

### Basic Pattern

```vue
<InputText
  v-model="value"
  :pt="{
    root: { class: 'bg-muted/30 hover:bg-muted/40 transition-[background-color,border-color,box-shadow,color] duration-md' }
  }"
/>

<Select
  v-model="selected"
  :options="options"
  :pt="{
    root: { class: 'text-foreground' },
    panel: { class: 'bg-card shadow-md border border-solid border-border' },
    item: { class: 'hover:bg-primary-light text-foreground transition-[background-color,color] duration-md' }
  }"
/>
```

### `<InputText>` with Focus Ring (Explicit)

```vue
<InputText
  v-model="email"
  type="email"
  :pt="{
    root: {
      class: 'bg-background ring-focus-focus transition-[background-color,border-color,box-shadow,color] duration-md'
    }
  }"
/>
```

### `<Select>` Full Example (Expanded)

```vue
<Select
  v-model="selectedRegion"
  :options="regions"
  option-label="name"
  placeholder="Select region"
  :pt="{
    root: { class: 'text-foreground' },
    label: { class: 'text-foreground text-sm' },
    panel: { class: 'bg-card shadow-md border border-solid border-border' },
    item: { class: 'text-sm text-foreground hover:bg-primary-light transition-[background-color,color] duration-md' },
    emptyMessage: { class: 'text-muted-foreground text-sm' }
  }"
/>
```

