## FORBIDDEN Patterns (Detailed)

### FORBIDDEN: Hardcoded Inline Styles

```vue
<InputText :style="{ background: '#ffffff', border: '1px solid #ccc' }" />
<Select :style="{ color: 'rgb(0,0,0)' }" />
```

Why forbidden:
1. Breaks theme token cascade
2. Breaks dark mode parity
3. Creates maintainability drift

### FORBIDDEN: Overriding PrimeVue internals in `<style scoped>`

```vue
<style scoped>
.p-button { background: #3b82f6 !important; }
.p-select-panel { background: white; }
.p-inputtext:focus { border-color: #6366f1; }
</style>
```

Why forbidden:
1. Scoped styles cannot reliably follow theme variable switching
2. Defeats central preset behavior
3. Causes specificity wars and `!important` escalation

### FORBIDDEN: Raw CSS Variable References in component style blocks

```vue
<style scoped>
.my-input { background: var(--surface-ground); color: var(--text-color); }
</style>
```

Use semantic token classes via `:pt` instead.

